Program: Discovery
Title: Hair - what is it good for?
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryxl
Last Broadcast Date: 31 January 2005
Why we have hair, and how hairstyles can change the way we are perceived. We are the most hairless of all the mammals, the so-called 'naked ape'. Theories are that we lost our hair to control parasitic infections. Picture: Punk hairstyles Credit: Getty Images